# tRPC entry-only rule

Even though tRPC runs inside Next.js (`apps/frontoffice`), it must remain a thin entry layer.

## Allowed in routers/route handlers
- Auth + tenancy extraction (`userId`, `orgId`)
- Input validation (Zod)
- Calling service layer functions
- Mapping service results to API outputs

## Forbidden
- Business logic / domain decisions
- Cypher or Neo4j queries
- Direct use of Neo4j driver
- Direct OpenAI calls
- Writing files / processing media

## Pattern
- `router -> service -> repository`
- Routers must depend on services only.

